('Decimal_And_Fraction_Conversion', 'C', 114, 'To convert a decimal to a fraction, firstly, express the decimal as a fraction with denominator depending on its place value. Then simplify the fraction to its lowest term. ; Example: 3.28 = 3\\[\\frac{28}{100}\\] = 3\\[\\frac{7}{25}\\] ; Do the opposite to convert fraction to decimal.'),
