('Multiples', 'C', 114, 'When a number is multiplied by another number, the result is a multiple of the first number. ; For example: ; 4 x 1 = 4 ; 4 x 2 = 8 ; 4 x 3 = 12 ; 4 x 4 = 16 ; 4, 8, 12, 16 are some multiples of 4. ; Some multiples of 4 are: 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 28, 32, 36,... ; Some multiples of 6 are: 6, 12, 18, 24, 30, 36,.. ; Some of the common mutiples of 4 and 6 are: 12, 24, 36,...'),
